
{{alias}}( x )
    Computes the arccosecant of a number.
    The domain of the inverse hyperbolic cotangent is the union of the intervals
    (-inf,0) and (0,inf).
    else function returns NaN

    Parameters
    ----------
    x: number
        Input value.

    Returns
    -------
    y: number
        inverse hyperbolic cosecant(in radians).

    Examples
    --------
    > var y = {{alias}}( 2.0 )
    ~0.48
    > y = {{alias}}( {{alias:@stdlib/constants/float64/pi}} )
    ~0.31
    > y = {{alias}}( -{{alias:@stdlib/constants/float64/pi}} )
    ~-0.31
    > y = {{alias}}( NaN )
    NaN
